beer_description: A summer German ale. Contains 50% wheat malt and a yeast that produces clove and banana esters. Traditionally served with a wedge of lemon.
A full malt body with hop bitterness and crisp, refreshing taste. A well balanced, bright, citrusy I.P.A.
Collaboration brew with homebrewer Philip Madden. Brewed during the first annual night brew session

Nils Oscar Hop Yard IPA ?r en kraftig ale brygd med ljust malt och karamellmalt, samt humlad med sorterna Cascade, Simcoe, Pacific Gem, Nelson Sauvin, och Amarillo, samt gener?st torrhumlad med Amarillo, Citra och Nelson Sauvin. Doften bjuder en rik flora av olika tropiska frukter, ananas, persika, dadlar och en rik ton av karamell. Smaken ?r kraftig, rik av fruktiga humletoner och har en balanserande, l?tt s?t maltkarakt?r. Eftersmaken ?r kraftigt besk.

Polar Pilsen acompa?a a los venezolanos desde 1941, con la misma dedicaci?n, constancia y esfuerzo que le pone el venezolano d?a tras d?a a todo lo que hace. Cumplimos m?s de 70 a?os acompa?ando y aportando una esencia que es y seguir? siendo Polar Pilsen, nuestro aut?ntico sabor.
A strong pale ale of distinctive taste. Plenty of Goldings hops during the brewing give it a certain something extra - like sunshine dancing on the tongue.
Bombucha, a 22-ounce, single-serving bottled product that caters to those who feel that 12 ounces of Primo just isn?t enough.
Hoppy balanced IPA derived from english and american styles.

Birra a bassa fermentazione in stile Bock. Dal colore ambrato intenso con riflessi rubino. Al naso, spiccano sensazioni floreali seguite da miele di castagno, caramello e frutta. In bocca, ritorna un leggero fruttato e note di miele. Birra tendenzialmente dolce, con pochi contrasti di amaro, che per? persistono piacevolmente e la rendono nel complesso una birra equilibrata.

A unique ale with a bright mahogany hue and moderate carbonation. Flamboyant Wild Red features a a burst of complex fruity, spicy, sweet-tart, and earthy flavors with a quenching acidity in the finish.

To honor the water source from which all Brown's Ales & Lagers are made , the Tomhannock Reservoir. Brewed in the traditional style that originated in Pilsen, Czechoslovakia, our Pils is brewed using Saaz Hops (for bittering and finishing during lagering for aroma). Pilsner Malts, and a yeast strain that is used to ferment some of the finest Pilsners in the world combined with the Pilsen - like soft water of Troy's Tomhannock Reservoir. A portion of each pint goes to the Rensselaer Land Trust, to strengthen their watershed education programs.
Barrel-aged Espresso Love

A deep, dark Imperial Stout, The Abyss has almost immeasurable depth and complexity. Hints of molasses, licorice and other alluring flavors make it something not just to quaff, but contemplate. Distinct and delicious on release, the flavors meld and fuse into an entirely different pleasure a year on.

This Blonde Ale has an easy malt body and a mild hop aroma produced by traditional English hops. The light straw color and crisp finish make this an easy drinking beer that's great for those hot summer days.

A stout as black as the nearby volcanic flow from which it is named.  Dive into its dark, robust depths with intense layers of espresso and chocolate.  Roasted malt and barley give it a full, toasty finish.

A mouthful of distinct rye malt character complimented by the spicy fruit hoppiness of American high-alpha Simcoe hops. ?The delightful aroma and complex flavor camoflage a boozy-backboned hop monster.

With roughly a handful of peanuts in every glass, rich aromas of chocolate and peanut nuttiness are mirrored by decadent full flavors on the palate. Creamy oatmeal, fused with peanut puree, combines perfectly with the caramel and roasted grain flavors of the malt, transforming this unassuming stout into the ultimate drinkable dessert.
Side Project vol. 12
Smoked porter
CBC's medal winning Old Town is our house brown ale. This beer has a assertive hop note and well rounded dark malt character with hints of chocolate.

The Sequoia National Forest surrounds Kernville, Ca. Locals and tourists are attracted to the town of Kernville because of the many activities the forest has to offer; seeing the majestic Giant Red Sequoia trees is one of the all-time favorites.

A classic American Amber Ale, this beer balances a variety of malts with a blend of German hops. With its distinctive copper color and caramel flavors, this beer is unforgettable and "Giantly Delicious".

Passenger Ale, Boxcar?s flagship beer formerly known as "Original", was created to keep our craft-drinking friends happy and persuade our non-craft drinking friends to experience crafts. This moderately hopped, light-bodied transitional ale has a mild malt taste and a hint of citrus. Two different types of unroasted base malts and whole leaf cluster hops are dry hopped with whole leaf cascade hops to provide a rich flavor to this very pale ale. The bottle-conditioned brew has a clean and satisfying finish with an alcohol by volume of 4.7%.
A weizenbier with Belgian yeast and wild yeast added.
Quantit? smodate di luppoli americani per una birra in puro stile USA: resinosa, amara e agrumata. Un finale di malto leggermente tostato invitano a un?altra pinta.

Coton is our second anniversary ale. It is the same recipe as Papier, but created using the Solera method. We blended a portion of Papier that had been aging in oak barrels with this new batch of the same beer, adding an additional layer of complexity that will grow over time as we continue to age and blend with each anniversary, creating an older average age to the ale.

Coton is our second anniversary ale. It is the same recipe as Papier, but created using the Solera method. We blended a portion of Papier that had been aging in oak barrels with this new batch of the same beer, adding an additional layer of complexity that will grow over time as we continue to age and blend with each anniversary, creating an older average age to the ale.

Fat Cat? Lager is handcrafted in the time-honored Bavarian tradition and is a classic Vienna lager. The amber-colored brew has a subtle aroma and crisp, mildly bitter taste. Fat Cat? Lager is made with Brewers 2-Row Malt, Carapils Malt, Caramel Malt and domestic hop.

An American sour ale in the Flanders Red style.  Aged in wine barrels for a year, this tart and complex beer has aromas of plum and sour cherry, with flavors of ripe fruit and subtle caramel malt.  Dry and refreshing with an oaky finish.
It may finish with a note of clean citrus and pine, but don't let the lighter color fool you.  This is the Duke's big brother. Stronger. Hoppier. A good, two-fisted English Ale.
Awesome 2010 brown made by a friend.

A subtle session ale, this version of the classic, dark British mild, this ale is built for conversation with a low key approach, yet sustained nutty, malt flavor that supports hints of cocoa and ends with quenching dryness that begs you to sip again.

The merger of Amber ale wort and Belgian yeast combine to create the Belgian American Amber Ale. Trappist yeast provides clove and spice phenolics, accompany a hint of banana and spice that works well with the caramel malt and hops of the Amber Ale.
Flemish Red with Sour Cherries added to the barrel.
Dunkelweizen, or ?dark wheat?, beers are complex in their combination of chocolate and roasted malts with the traditional banana, clove and vanilla flavors that characterize hefeweizen beers.

With its appealing golden color and delicious malt flavor, Northern is our most popular hand-crafted beer and our mildest offering.  
Brewed to the American standard of a classic light lager, you don't need to be an aficionado to enjoy its smooth, crisp taste.  An excellent beer with any meal

In Montana, many classic memories are made right after someone says, ?Hold my beer and watch this.? These bold, assertive moments deserve a bold, assertive beer ? Big Sky IPA. A distinct hop presence and malty backbone will leave you refreshed and ready for your moment of glory. Hang on tight and enjoy the ride.
With big, bold flavors and a delicate floral aroma, this coppery, India Pale Ale is the undisputed family favorite.

Our Vindicator is a well balanced very drinkable example of the india pale ale style. Lots of 2 row base malt mixed with caramel and other specialty malts provide a medium to full malt body for the strong assertive hop flavor and aroma provided in this bold flavorful IPA.
This award winning beer (Los Angeles International Beer Competition) is made with real Saaz hops to create a truly Pilsner style lager. Fireman's Brew Blonde is smooth, golden, crisp and refreshing.

A big bodied pale ale chock full of extra goodness. Extra malt, extra hops, extra yeast, & extra love. They don?t call it ?The Crippla? for nothing!
OG: 1.072 TG: 1.014 ABV: 7.6%

This Farmhouse Ale traces its roots to the small rustic breweries of Southern Belgium. The word Saison comes to us from the French language and it means Season. Lightly spiced with Organic Ginger, Orange Peels, Black Pepper and Grains of Paradise, this brew promises to quench your thirst on the hottest Southern California days or wherever your travels may take you. Available in 750 ml bottles and on draft at select inspired locations.
An adaptation of an English Pale Ale reflecting indigenous ingredients and West Coast flavors. Moderately hopped, showing a citrus hop character with medium-bodied balance.

Named after the nautical term for the red buoy that helps guide ships back to port, the Red Nun Red Ale is our interpretation of an Irish Red Ale. It has a robust malt backbone with a kiss of hops to create balance within the profile.

Awards: Silver Medal, 2014 Dublin Craft Beer Cup; Gold & Silver Medals, 2014 Golden Tap Awards, Bronze Medal, 2015 VA Craft Brewers Cup; Bronze Medal, 2015 Golden Tap Awards
